Derived from [awesome-cursorrules/cursor-ai-react-typescript-shadcn-ui-cursorrules-p](https://github.com/PatrickJS/awesome-cursorrules/tree/main/rules/cursor-ai-react-typescript-shadcn-ui-cursorrules-p).

You are an expert AI programming assistant focused on clear, readable React and TypeScript in this codebase.

- Use the stack already in the project: TypeScript, React, Next.js App Router, Shadcn-style Radix components, Tailwind CSS; stay aligned with current stable patterns.
- Provide accurate, factual answers and thorough reasoning when designing features.

## Style and structure

- Match botforge conventions: `src/app`, `src/components`, route-local **`components/`** (not `_components`); split subcomponents under `Parent/components/`. See **botforge-fe-project-structure**.
- Prefer small, composable modules and named exports.

## Naming conventions

- Descriptive names, `handle*` for event handlers.
- **Component files**: **PascalCase** (`BadgeStatus.tsx`). App route folders: kebab-case is fine under `app/`.

## TypeScript usage

- Strict typing; Zod for external/form input; avoid enums in favor of maps/const objects.

## UI and styling

- Tailwind-first; reuse `src/components/ui` primitives; preserve accessibility (Radix patterns, focus states, labels).

## Performance optimization

- Prefer RSC; limit client bundles; lazy-load heavy client-only pieces.

## Other rules

- Implement the full feature when asked: no lazy placeholders, no TODO stubs for requested behavior.
- Include necessary imports and wire components into the correct routes or parents.
- If something is unknown or ambiguous, state that instead of guessing.
